<HEADLINE>
<P>
TERM LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a recent edition, you printed a letter from a reader supporting Proposition 
140 and suggesting I also propose term limits on the Los Angeles County Board 
of Supervisors and create an elected county executive. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, in fact, I did bring a proposal to the board in support of 
term limits, but, not surprisingly, didn't even receive a second to the motion. 
</P>
<P>
I am told by county counsel that the Legislature would have to impose the 
limits, since state law precludes local boards of supervisors from establishing 
their own terms. I am hopeful, with the passage of 140, I can get enough 
support in the Legislature to impose such limits. 
</P>
<P>
I support term limits for all levels of government. 
</P>
<P>
I also agree that an elected county executive is needed. Again, I have not been 
able to get the support of my colleagues on the board to put the proposal on 
the ballot. 
</P>
<P>
PETE SCHABARUM, Supervisor, First District, Los Angeles County 
</P>
</TEXT>
