<HEADLINE>
<P>
JACKS DASH IS FUTURITY WINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SCHUELEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Veteran trainer Rodney Hart called Jacks Dash the best 2-year-old he has ever 
handled after the bargain gelding won the $334,000 Golden State Futurity 
quarter-horse race Saturday night at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
It was the fifth consecutive victory for Jacks Dash since he was claimed for 
$12,500 at Los Alamitos on July 26. 
</P>
<P>
"This is the best 2-year-old I've ever had," said Hart, 57, who has trained at 
Los Alamitos since 1960. "He's really sound and doesn't have any problems." 
</P>
<P>
Jacks Dash broke alertly from post seven and led all the way in defeating 
Taking On The Cash, who was on the rail, by a head. Vital Sign finished third 
in the field of 10. STEVE SCHUELEIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
