<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Profits From Ohrbach Estate: Los Angeles dentist Gary Milan has sued Sotheby's 
auction house in New York on grounds that it breached an agreement to share 
profits with him from items auctioned from the estate of Jerome Ohrbach of 
Ohrbach's department stores. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles federal court suit said Sotheby's agreed in October, 1973, to 
give Milan a 20% commission on sales of property from the estate in return for 
helping Sotheby's obtain the account. The suit said Sotheby's repudiated the 
agreement in September, 1990. (Case No. 90- 6907. Filed Dec. 26, 1990.) 
