</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mike Brock and Eric Bailey 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GERRYMANDERED: The 3rd District will be a chore for county supervisors when 
they reapportion next year. 
</P>
<P>
(B1) It extends from La Habra to San Juan Capistrano and got that way in 1977, 
after then-Supervisor Ralph Clark decided his West Anaheim service station 
should be in his own 2nd District. . . . To accomplish it, he ceded the Santa 
Ana Canyon area to Supervisor Ralph Diedrich, who then pushed his 
Fullerton-based district south to the San Diego County line. Insiders said 
Diedrich wanted the South County development boom within his control. A 
not-unrelated fact: Diedrich later was convicted of exacting a bribe from a 
developer. Diedrich died in 1988. Mike Brock and Eric Bailey 
</P>
